A Durban man was rushed to hospital after falling from the fourth floor onto a concrete floor at a block of flats in Lagoon Drive in Umhlanga, Durban. Shawn Herbst, Netcare 911â€™s spokesperson, said the incident happened just before 9.30 am on Thursday. He said reports from the scene indicate that the 24-year-old man had fallen from the fourth floor, landing on the concrete below. When paramedics arrived on scene, Herbst said the man was found to have suffered critical injuries and was rushed to a local hospital after being stabilised. Herbst said circumstances leading to the man falling from the apartment are at this stage not known.